Happy Mother’s Day To All You Amazing Mommas Out There. Lord Knows What We Would Do Without You 🤍 

Btw if you are the Nashville area I would highly recommend checking out @colesnashville . Chris & I went there last night for dinner & it was amazing! Our good friends Bay & Coco just took it over has the new general managers. Great place & vibe! Perfect for date nights, a good place to take mom, or just go & get a drink & hang out. So Y’all go & show them some love! 🍽️ 

Selfie Brought To You By 📷: @christopherdelislemusic

Happy Birthday Mel 🥳 Mel turned 4 on Sunday (Mother’s Day). So we spent a big part of our weekend celebrating our favorite pup. She got all kinds of goodies & treats. Went to the groomer (aka The Spa) & to top it all off @rigdonretrievers made Mel a beautiful Birthday Cake. So I guess you can say we had a PAW-TY 😆🐾 🎂🎉🐶

We got Mel when she was about 8 weeks old from @rigdonretrievers & We so appreciate Brandy & the whole family & crew. So please check them out! Great people who love their dogs! 

We love Mel so much & our so grateful to have her in our lives. She is such a sweet & loving dog & definitely worth celebrating 🤍🐾

📷: @christopherdelislemusic

#womencrusheveryday #womeninmusic #newmusic #newmusicnow #countrymusic #ashtaylor #bakersfield #nashville #crazywomencountry #womensupportingwomen #wherewomensvoicesmatter #musicnews

THE ACOUSTIC SESSIONS- TRACK 2- FAMILY 🤍🎶

Family is a song I wrote by myself one night at my dining room table. I wrote it for my brothers because because we don’t always see the same way even though we have the same last name. You can listen to the track now on Spotify or wherever you like to stream music. Thanks again for all the love on this project. 
❤️🤍💙LINK IN BIO

THE ACOUSTIC SESSIONS-TRACK 3- PLAY LIKE KEN 🎸 

I wrote this song years ago when after a show one night a guy came up & told me I played guitar like a man. He was a super sweet southern teddy bear type & I just smiled & said well I don’t know what to tell you brother I guess I just look like Barbie & Play Like Ken. I wrote this song driving home that night. This was a blast to break it down & do an acoustic version of. You can listen to the track now on Spotify or wherever you like to stream music. Thank you so much for all the love on this project ❤️🤍💙 LINK IN BIO

New Nashville Lineup Announcement! 🚨
-
I'm excited to announce that @ashtaylorcountry will be part of our family showcase on October 21st at @nashhousetn!
-
Ash and I go back a little over 3 years. In that time, she's done so much for me and this family we call Southern Fellow. In so many ways she has been my adopted sister. She's always there to give advice, even when it's not always asked for.  Ash tolerates my sarcasm, yet still finds it in herself to lend an understanding ear. Simply put, Southern Fellow would not be the same without her.
-
When she is not putting up with me, Ash is a dang good songwriter. Her songs are grounded in real life just as she is. They reflect the joys and struggles of everyday people. Something I wish more country artists would get back to.
-
Come out to see Ash Taylor October 21st at NashHouse in Nashville, TN.
